sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1895999
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Jake Burton
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Hypothetical design for the 2016 Newcastle iGEM team.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: AraC
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: AraC operator, truncated to include araO1, araI1, araI2, c-amp1, and c-amp2 sites. This operator should *activate* transcription in the presence of AraC; b/c the operator lacks the araO2 site, there should not be araC-mediated repression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sara Neves (Fighting Darwins)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M36405
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a bicistronic RBS, which consists of a constitutive RBS, and a leader sequence that includes the second RBS. It uses bicistronic junction architecture to tightly control translation. It contains two ribosome binding sites: one controls the gene of interest, and the another synthesizes a short leader protein. The latter bicistronic's translation prevents the former RBS from forming a secondary structure with the gene of interest. This ensures a more consistent expression level of your gene of interest.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Justo A. Caballero, Shamik Mascharak and Sibel Sayiner
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: More information can be found at BIOFAB.org.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This RBS is of medium strength.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K090000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes the gene GluR0 from Synechocystis. It is a well characterised glutamate-gated K+ membrane channel, which has a considerable degree of structural and functional homology to rat neurone GluR2 AMPA receptors.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ellis O'Neill
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: From peptide sequence of Synechocystis PCC 6803, codon optimised for E.coli, restriction sites removed, and synthesised de novo.
